The paper proposes a learned image compression scheme based on deep neural networks, which involves bit-plane decomposition and bidirectional context disentanglement network. This work is primarily focused on image processing and computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory and machine learning, which could potentially fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for scalable image compression, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
